From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0015/N] assembler_aarch64.hpp: add Address(Register, intptr_t/uintptr_t) for CHERI

Same shape as patch 0010 (macroAssembler mov overload) but for the
`Address` ctor family. The existing seven `Address(Register, T)`
integer-disp ctors cover `int`/`long`/`long long` and unsigned
variants. Under CHERI/Morello purecap `intptr_t == __intcap` and
`uintptr_t == unsigned __intcap` — neither implicitly converts to
any of the existing overloads, giving `error: call to constructor
of 'Address' is ambiguous` at aarch64.ad:3888 and similar sites
that arithmetic-mix signed/unsigned cap values (e.g.
`offset - markWord::monitor_value`).

A single `intptr_t` overload is not enough: a `uintptr_t`-typed
argument still ties between `intptr_t` and `unsigned long long` (no
exact match). Add BOTH `intptr_t` and `uintptr_t` overloads so the
arg type matches one of them exactly.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0015)

--- a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/assembler_aarch64.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/assembler_aarch64.hpp
@@ -414,6 +414,16 @@
     : _base(r), _index(noreg), _offset(o), _mode(base_plus_offset), _target(0) { }
   Address(Register r, unsigned long long o)
     : _base(r), _index(noreg), _offset(o), _mode(base_plus_offset), _target(0) { }
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+  // On CHERI/Morello purecap, intptr_t / uintptr_t are __intcap / unsigned
+  // __intcap. None of the integer ctors above accept those, and a single
+  // overload still leaves the other signedness ambiguous. Provide both
+  // variants explicitly; each strips cap metadata to an int64_t offset.
+  Address(Register r, intptr_t o)
+    : _base(r), _index(noreg), _offset(static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uintptr_t>(o))), _mode(base_plus_offset), _target(0) { }
+  Address(Register r, uintptr_t o)
+    : _base(r), _index(noreg), _offset(static_cast<int64_t>(o)), _mode(base_plus_offset), _target(0) { }
+#endif
   Address(Register r, ByteSize disp)
     : Address(r, in_bytes(disp)) { }
   Address(Register r, Register r1, extend ext = lsl())
